author: Inside Edition
description: Charlie Sheen promises to drop explosive truth bombs in his new tell all documentary "aka Charlie Sheen." Now, in an Inside Edition exclusive, hear from his ex fiance who has her own shocking news. Brett Rossi met Sheen in 2013 after a mutual friend told her Sheen was enamored by her work as an adult film star. Sheen later proposed, but she says when he started using drugs, their relationship turned violent. Sheen has denied this.
title: Brett Rossi, Charlie Sheen's Ex, Speaks Out in Exclusive Interview

author: Inside Edition
description: A proud family beamed from the stands. Archie Wilson, 19, moved from his home in Australia to play football at the University of Nebraska. Last month he broke down in tears when a reporter asked what he missed most about being far from home. His dad, Lee Wilson, mom Jessica, and their sons made the 9,198-mile trip from Australia to see the athlete. His family is in the stadium in Lincoln along with 91,000 fans. Inside Edition producer Emma Keady was there.
title: Family of Football Player Travels Over 9,000 Miles to Watch Game

author: Inside Edition
description: Inside Edition spoke to mathematician Tim Shar-Tier for some tips on how to win at Powerball. Suggestions include buying in bulk and avoiding lucky numbers.
title: Tips for Winning at Powerball #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: To say this suspect was uncooperative is an understatement. The Lee County Sheriff's Office in Florida was called to assist some homeowners with an unusual intruder, which surprised even the responding deputy. Once the shock of seeing a 300 pound wild boar in the living room wore off, deputies had to figure out how to bring it out peacefully. But the beast wasn't going to go quietly. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 300-Pound Wild Boar Breaks Into Home by Crashing Through Screen Door

author: Inside Edition
description: Trump posted a distorted image of the comedian on Truth Social saying her U.S. citizenship may be revoked. O'Donnell fought back.
title: Can Trump Revoke Rosie O'Donnell's Citizenship? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: At just 13 years old, a young fisherman made the catch of a lifetime! Jackson Denio was on a deep sea fishing trip off the coast of New Hampshire. That's when he nabbed a halibut weighing 177 pounds! Despite the fish having 50 pounds on him, the teen was determined to reel it in himself. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 13-Year-Old Reels in 177 Pound Halibut on Fishing Trip
